                              ወአቅላሲያ፡ ዘነበሩ፡ በንሂሳ፡ ስሉስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ [fol. 95vb] ነፍሑ፡ በውስተ፡ ከርሣ። ተወልደ፡ እምኔሆሙ፡
                              ቀናየ፡ አናብስት፡ ፷ከመ፡ አምላኩ፡ ዘይሠሪ፡ አበሣ።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/> The poem is probably written in the main hand. </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#96ra">Fol. 96ra</locus>-rb: Excerpt from a miracle of
                           Mary about the cannibal of Qǝmǝr (bälaʾe säbʾ).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/> The excerpt is probably written in the main hand. </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-signs (in the shape of +) indicating the place
                           where the omissions, written interlineally (fol. 10va) or in the margins
                           (fol. 5vb, 22ra), belong.&#xD; - Omitted letters are written
                           interlineally: fol. 9ra, 35rb, 51rb, 64vb.&#xD; - Spaces for rubricated
                           names of the donor(s) are left unfilled: fols. 14rb, 51va, 76va, 78va,
                           79va, 85vb.&#xD; - Scribbles: fols. 1v, 2r, 3r, 80r, 95v.</item>
                     </list>
